# PX4 Control

This folder contains the source files related to PX4 offboard control for the Robotics AI project.

PX4 is used as the flight control system in this project. It allows the simulated drone to receive movement commands and respond to mission-level decisions generated by the ROS 2 system.

## Purpose of This Folder

The main purpose of this folder is to connect the AI decision output with the drone movement control.

In this project, the AI decision layer generates mission states such as:

- `SEARCH`
- `INVESTIGATE`
- `CONFIRM_HOVER`

The PX4 control node uses these mission states and converts them into drone position setpoints. These setpoints are then published to PX4 command topics so that the drone can move according to the selected mission state.

## Main Functionality

The PX4 control layer publishes commands to topics such as:

- `/fmu/in/offboard_control_mode`
- `/fmu/in/trajectory_setpoint`
- `/fmu/in/vehicle_command`

These topics are used to enable offboard control mode, send trajectory setpoints, and provide vehicle commands to the simulated drone.

## Why PX4 Control Is Important

PX4 control is important because it acts as the connection between decision-making and physical movement.

Without this layer, the AI decision module would only produce mission states, but the drone would not know how to move based on those states.

This folder helps demonstrate how high-level robotics decisions can be converted into low-level flight control commands.

## Role in the Project

This folder represents the control part of the robotics AI pipeline.

